Section 17: Spring JMS Support
 Lecture 93: Define Consumer JMS service


1. Create New Package for JMS (Message listener)
 - ej.springframework.services.jms
 1.1 Create New Class
  - ej.springframework.services.jms.TextMessageListener.java
 1.2 Add @Component annotation on the TextMessageListener class
 1.3 Create and implements new method on the TextMessageListener.java
 1.3 Add @JmsListener annotation
  - @JmsListener(destination = "text.messagequeue")
  - Note that "text.messagequeue" copy from JMSConfig.java and paste it.

2. Start Server and Text Message services
 1.1 Check the Tomcat Server console
 1.2 Open the http://localhost:8080/product/list
 1.3 Click any product view function
 1.4. Check message in the Sever Console box